Despite this, 100% of fourth graders achieved excellent results in the 2008 State Mathematics Exam.
Equally impressive is that 93% of fourth graders passed the English Language and Literature exam.
This incredible achievement has not been achieved with the instrument that Obama would prefer.
Sixth Street focuses on repetition, practice, continuous assessment of skills and rejection of objections.
In addition, and this is what Obama should consider, according to Linda Mikels, director of Sixth Street, the school’s educational principle is the “full immersion” of English students into the language environment.
The essence of the immersion method is the almost exclusive use of the English language in teaching other subjects.
Mikels, who is opposed to bilingual education, said: “We’ve had a tremendous success in saying that if someone walked into a classroom, they wouldn’t know who the student was who had just arrived from Mexico 12 months earlier.”
