By the age of 35, Gebrselassie set the 26th world record for his career in such a wide range of fields that he won the World Championships or reached a world record in almost every race from the 1500m to the marathon.
Last month Gebrselassie skipped the Beijing Olympic marathon, fearing that air pollution would aggravate his asthmatic problems.
