In almost perfect conditions - sunny weather, initially at 9<0xC2><0xB0>C and finally at 13<0xC2><0xB0>C - Gebrselassie won on Sunday, at an incredible speed of 2 minutes and 56 seconds per kilometre.
Since non-marathon runners such as Gebrselassie and the Kenyan Paul Tergat turned to longer distances, the marathon record has declined by more than two minutes in the last decade since the Brazilian Ronaldo da Costa won in Berlin in 1998 with a 2:06:05 result.
