Not all internet users are aware of the fact that when searching the Internet, the search terms are recorded exactly, from which IP address they were searched and to which page they went after the search.
For example, the Personalized Search, launched two years ago, allows users to store their own surfing history, to look back on what they were looking for, what they clicked on, and to generate much more personalized results for them in the long run - the same logic will be used in the Recommendations, which is used to offer us products and services based on our previously stated and recorded preferences.
What if they use my data against me when they look at what I’m doing?, users who are worried about seeing Google’s data monopoly ask.
In most cases, the degree of potential power represented by the company can be frightening, not guilt, fear of punishment, desire for freedom, or rebellion against power, which triggers counter-reactions among internet users.
However, it is a confirmed fact that all searched terms are not only recorded, but in justified cases they can also be transferred to third parties, in such cases the privacy rights of Internet users are not protected by anything.
Perhaps the loudest example of this in recent times has been a coordinated action against Brazilian pedophiles, during which Google provided the Brazilian government with information about pedophiles from its social network Orkut, which allows it to identify them.
However, internet users concerned about privacy sighed in May, when the company, along with the EFF, successfully proved their truth in court against the FBI, saying that Google could not be forced by any part of the constitution to disclose any information that the FBI was secretly asking for.
