Workplace accidents: Napolitano says prevention is more important than anything else
Every day in Italy, 2,500 accidents occur at work, of which 3 result in death and 27 result in permanent disability.
According to data from the occupational accident insurance company, there were nearly 1,200 deaths in the workplace in 2007.
The figures show the seriousness of a phenomenon that is still one of the most common causes of death today, and which requires almost twice as many deaths as homicide.
