In-school initiatives aimed at directly educating young people on the verge of entering the world of work are of paramount importance.
It is our duty to maintain interest in this phenomenon, not to let the social importance of this issue diminish, and we need more effective legislation that needs to be enforced.
The president of the House of Commons, Gianfranco Fini, said: “The grave social significance of workplace accidents that result in death weighs on the conscience of all of us, and the institutions are required to put an end to it as soon as possible.”
